  <script>
    (window as any).dataLayer = (window as any).dataLayer || [];
    (window as any).gtag = function () {
      (window as any).dataLayer.push(arguments);
    };
    (window as any).gtag("js", new Date());
    (window as any).gtag("config", "G-3TXVE0LR1X");
  </script>
  <title>{pageTitle}</title>
  <meta charset="utf-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1, shrink-to-fit=no" />
  <meta
    name="description"
    content="Improve root growth and thicken your lawn with aeration and seeding services in Lynchburg, VA."
  />
  <meta
    name="keywords"
    content="aeration lynchburg, overseeding service, lawn seeding, soil compaction relief"
  />
  <link id="favicon" rel="icon" type="image/png" href="/assets/favicon.ico" />
  <link
    href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Lato:300,400,700&display=swap"
    rel="stylesheet"
  />
  <link
    href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Poppins:300,400,500,600,700,800,900"
    rel="stylesheet"
  />
  <link
    rel="stylesheet"
    href="https://stackpath.bootstrapcdn.com/font-awesome/4.7.0/css/font-awesome.min.css"
  />
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/animate.css" />
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/owl.carousel.min.css" />
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/owl.theme.default.min.css" />
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/magnific-popup.css" />
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/ionicons.min.css" />
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/flaticon.css" />
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/icomoon.css" />
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/style.css" />
</head>
<body>
  <TopBar />

  <Navigation />
  <main class="service-page service-page--compact">
    <section
      class="service-hero service-hero--trugreen service-hero--compact"
      style="background-image: url('/assets/Aeration_Service.jpg');"
    >
      <div class="container">
        <div class="row">
          <div class="col-lg-9 col-xl-7 hero-content-block">
            <h1 class="mb-2">Aeration & Seeding</h1>
            <h2 class="mb-3">Improve root growth and thicken your lawn.</h2>
            <p class="mb-4 lead">
              Aeration relieves compacted soil so water and nutrients reach the roots.
              Overseeding fills thin areas for a fuller, healthier lawn over time.
            </p>
            <a href="/contact" class="btn btn-primary">Get a Free Quote</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="service-section service-section--compact">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="row align-items-center gutter-40">
          <div class="col-lg-6">
            <h2 class="mb-3">What’s Included With Aeration & Seeding</h2>
            <ul class="checklist">
              <li>Core aeration across the lawn</li>
              <li>Overseeding with quality grass seed</li>
              <li>Lawn condition evaluation</li>
              <li>Aftercare recommendations for best results</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="col-lg-6">
            <figure class="service-image-card">
              <img
                src="/assets/Aeration_Service.jpg"
                alt="Aeration equipment working on a lawn"
                loading="lazy"
              />
              <figcaption>
                <h3>Thicker, healthier turf</h3>
                <p>Aeration and overseeding restore density and improve lawn performance.</p>
              </figcaption>
            </figure>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="service-section service-section--compact">
      <div class="container">
        <h2 class="mb-3">Why Aeration & Seeding Matters</h2>
        <ul class="bullet-list">
          <li>Improves water penetration and reduces runoff</li>
          <li>Encourages stronger roots and healthier turf</li>
          <li>Fills thin spots for a thicker lawn</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="service-section service-section--compact">
      <div class="container">
        <h2 class="mb-3">How It Works</h2>
        <ol class="bullet-list">
          <li><strong>Assess:</strong> We evaluate compaction, thinning, and goals.</li>
          <li><strong>Service:</strong> We aerate, then overseed for better coverage.</li>
          <li><strong>Finish:</strong> We provide aftercare steps to maximize results.</li>
        </ol>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="service-section service-section--compact">
      <div class="container">
        <h2 class="mb-3">Best Time to Schedule</h2>
        <p>Often scheduled in fall (and sometimes spring) depending on grass type and local conditions.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="service-section service-section--compact">
      <div class="container">
        <h2 class="mb-4">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

        <h3>How soon will I see results?</h3>
        <p>
          Germination timing varies based on seed type, watering, and weather. Many lawns show improvement within a few weeks,
          with bigger improvements over the following months.
        </p>

        <h3>Do I need to water after seeding?</h3>
        <p>
          Yes. Consistent watering is one of the most important factors for success. We’ll provide guidance based on conditions.
        </p>

        <h3>Can you aerate without seeding?</h3>
        <p>
          Yes. Aeration alone still helps relieve compaction. Seeding is recommended when lawns are thin or patchy.
        </p>

        <h3>Should I mow before aeration?</h3>
        <p>
          Typically, yes. A slightly shorter mow helps aeration and improves seed-to-soil contact when overseeding.
        </p>

        <h3>Will plugs left on the lawn be messy?</h3>
        <p>
          The soil plugs break down naturally and return nutrients to the lawn. They usually disappear after mowing and rainfall.
        </p>

        <h3>Can you aerate if I have irrigation?</h3>
        <p>
          Yes, but it’s important to identify sprinkler heads and shallow lines. Let us know so we can take proper precautions.
        </p>

        <h3>Does aeration help drainage?</h3>
        <p>
          Aeration can improve absorption and reduce runoff in compacted soil. Severe drainage issues may require additional solutions.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="service-section service-section--compact">
      <div class="container">
        <h2 class="mb-3">Related Aeration & Seeding Articles</h2>
        <ul class="bullet-list">
          <li><a href="/blog/is-lawn-aeration-worth-it">Is Lawn Aeration Worth It?</a></li>
          <li><a href="/blog/best-time-to-aerate-and-seed-in-virginia">Best Time to Aerate and Seed in Virginia</a></li>
          <li><a href="/blog/overseeding-tips-for-thicker-grass">Overseeding Tips for Thicker Grass</a></li>
          <li><a href="/blog/how-to-water-after-overseeding">How to Water After Overseeding</a></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="service-section service-section--compact bg-light">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="callout-panel">
          <h2>Get a Free Quote</h2>
          <p>Tell us your lawn size and current condition and we’ll recommend the best approach.</p>
          <a href="/contact" class="btn btn-primary">Request a Free Quote</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

  <Footer />

  <div id="ftco-loader" class="show fullscreen">
    <svg class="circular" width="48px" height="48px">
      <circle class="path-bg" cx="24" cy="24" r="22" fill="none" stroke-width="4" stroke="#eeeeee"
      ></circle>
      <circle
        class="path"
        cx="24"
        cy="24"
        r="22"
        fill="none"
        stroke-width="4"
        stroke-miterlimit="10"
        stroke="#F96D00"></circle>
    </svg>
  </div>

  <script src="/js/jquery.min.js" is:inline></script>
  <script src="/js/jquery-migrate-3.0.1.min.js" is:inline></script>
  <script src="/js/popper.min.js" is:inline></script>
  <script src="/js/bootstrap.min.js" is:inline></script>
  <script src="/js/jquery.easing.1.3.js" is:inline></script>
  <script src="/js/jquery.waypoints.min.js" is:inline></script>
  <script src="/js/jquery.stellar.min.js" is:inline></script>
  <script src="/js/owl.carousel.min.js" is:inline></script>
  <script src="/js/jquery.magnific-popup.min.js" is:inline></script>
  <script src="/js/scrollax.min.js" is:inline></script>
  <script
    src="https://maps.googleapis.com/maps/api/js?key=AIzaSyBVWaKrjvy3MaE7SQ74_uJiULgl1JY0H2s&sensor=false"
  ></script>
  <script src="/js/google-map.js" is:inline></script>
  <script src="/js/main.js" is:inline></script>
</body>
